gomodel:SYNGO_5274  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1a,b: Mind Bomb-1 (MIB1) was identified in PSD biochemical fractions by by mass-spectrometry and MIB1 was enriched in PSD fraction as compared to synaptosomal and presynaptic fractions from Rat forebrains.\n\nFigure 1c-e: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for MIB1 and PSD-95 (DLG4) in 21DIV cultured hippocampal neurons showed partial co-localization.\n\nFigure 1j: immunoelectron microscopy of MIB1 confirmed localization to PSD and nearby vesicle-like structures in adult mouse cortex.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"The immunoelectron microscopy of Mib1, using a section of adult mouse cortex and diaminobenzidine as a chromagen\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5274" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

